August seems very unlikely. 
The 2nd dose increase equals pretty much the 1st dose increase 5 weeks earlier. Thus the 2nd dose increase from August 10 to August 31 will probably correspond to the 1st dose increase from July 6 and July 27, which was 2.1 points. So, 75.0+2.1= 77.1 would be the quick and dirty prediction for end of August. Not even sure if 80% is secured for September …
@belikewater @paulm @probahilliby : Is this potential wisdom against the crowd or just foolish oversimplification?

60% second dose was reached on the 22 June;
60% first dose was reached on the 5 April;
there were 78 days in between.
80% first dose was reached on the 16 June; +78 days it is 2 September. Assuming a Gaussian distribution is closed enough to being split half half between August and September. Though I will weight it a little further in time given possible slow downs and previous estimate method.
